description: The Princeton Sentry Ginkgo (Ginkgo biloba 'Princeton Sentry') is an amazing and attractive species of tree suitable for a variety of uses. Its attractive, fan-shaped foliage is medium green in color, turning a brilliant yellow in the fall. Its oval-shaped crown offers filtered shade and makes it a great choice for street-side planting where its lush foliage can be appreciated. It has a very strong and durable trunk and is highly resistant to storm damage, while its roots remain strong and wide, making it ideal for tight spaces like small yards. Its strong resilience to air pollution and ability to thrive in a variety of soil types is unmatched, making it a great low maintenance choice.
